bibl.note: Our transcription is based on a digital image of the microfilmed original.

div1.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Wahington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.

The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting: We command you, 'that you have the body of Leonard Martin by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Leonard Martin shall be called or charged, before the HON. ROGER S. GREENE, Judge of the aforesaid Court at the City of Seattle, in the Court House on the 21st day of May 1885 at 9.30 AD of said day to do and receive whay shall then and there be considered concerning him the said Leonard Martin And have you then ad there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. ROGER S. GREENE. Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 20th day of May A.D. 1855
JAMES SEAVEY, Clerk By James P Ludlow Deputy
